      "summary": "The Citizens Foundation USA (TCF-USA) is a highly efficient educational nonprofit dedicated to <cite id=\"1\">building civil society in Pakistan</cite> by providing quality education to underprivileged children. Since its <cite id=\"2\">founding in 1995</cite>, the organization has established a robust infrastructure that currently provides <cite id=\"3\">operational support for 534 schools</cite>. TCF-USA operates with exceptional financial discipline, maintaining a <cite id=\"4\">program expense ratio of 89.5%</cite>, which ensures that nearly all contributions directly fund educational initiatives. The organization's model is comprehensive, encompassing <cite id=\"5\">new school construction</cite>, teacher training, and <cite id=\"6\">higher education scholarships</cite> to ensure long-term student success. Beyond academics, TCF-USA has demonstrated environmental leadership by <cite id=\"7\">converting schools to solar energy</cite>, reducing operational costs and carbon footprints. The charity holds a <cite id=\"8\">99.33/100 overall score from Charity Navigator</cite> and a <cite id=\"9\">Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite>, reflecting its commitment to accountability and rigorous outcome tracking.",
